businessElements.name: AllergyConcernContainer
businessElements.description: A container for organizing the clients's allergies and adverse reactions that are related to one another. Specific observations of problems or other clinical statements captured at a point in time are wrapped into this a Allergy Concern

businessElements.name: AllergyConcernStartDate
businessElements.description: The date the Allergy Concern was first recorded.

businessElements.name: AllergyObservationAllergyTypeCode
businessElements.description: A code for the specific Type of Allergy observed

businessElements.name: AllergyObservationContainer
businessElements.description: A container for organizing all of the specific assessments and treatments of a patient for a specific allergy / adverse reaction Concern.

businessElements.name: AllergyObservationID
businessElements.description: a unique identifier assigned by an administrative body to the specific allergy observation

businessElements.name: AllergyReactionContainer
businessElements.description: A container holding Business Elements associated with each reaction observed in a specific observation. There may be multiple reactions observed in a specific observation.

businessElements.name: AllergyReactionID
businessElements.description: The identifier assigned by the administrative body to the observation of an allergy reaction.

businessElements.name: AllergyReactionNotes
businessElements.description: Notes (unstructured text) describing the reaction by the observer

businessElements.name: AllergyReactionSeverityValue
businessElements.description: A code representing the severity of the specific Allergy reaction

businessElements.name: AllergyReactionValue
businessElements.description: A code representing the type of Allergy reaction

businessElements.name: AllergyObservationSeverityNotes
businessElements.description: Notes on the severity of the allergy reaction

businessElements.name: AllergyObservationSeverityValue
businessElements.description: A code representing the severity of the reactions to a specific allergen

businessElements.name: PatientAdministrationGenderCode
businessElements.description: A code describing the gender of the Patient used in making administrative decisions.

businessElements.name: PatientBirthPlaceAddress
businessElements.description: The address where the Patient was born

businessElements.name: PatientDateOfBirth
businessElements.description: The date of birth of the Patient

businessElements.name: PatientEthnicityCode
businessElements.description: The code representing the ethnicity specified by the Patient

businessElements.name: PatientHomeAddress
businessElements.description: The home address for the Patient

businessElements.name: PatientHomePhone
businessElements.description: The home telephone number for the Patient

businessElements.name: PatientID
businessElements.description: An identifier that applies to this person as a Patient.

businessElements.name: PatientLanguageAbilityCode
businessElements.description: A code indicating the Patient's ability with specific language.

businessElements.name: PatientLanguageCode
businessElements.description: A code representing a language used to communicate with the Patient

businessElements.name: PatientLanguageContainer
businessElements.description: A container used to so that associates individual Business Elements associated with a specific language in which a Patient may be able to communicate.

businessElements.name: PatientLanguagePerferenceIndicator
businessElements.description: Used to indicate (Yes) this is the language to be used in communicating with the Patient

businessElements.name: PatientMaritalStatus
businessElements.description: A code specifying Patient's current domestic partnership status.

businessElements.name: PatientName
businessElements.description: the name the Patient normally uses

businessElements.name: PatientRace
businessElements.description: A code for a race of the Patient specified by the Patient

businessElements.name: PatientReligousAffliationCode
businessElements.description: The code representing the religous afflication specified by the Patient

businessElements.name: MedicationAdministeredDosageRate
businessElements.description: Identifies the speed with which the medication was introduced into the patient. Typically the rate for an infusion e.g. 200ml in 2 hours. May also expressed as a rate per unit of time such as 100ml per hour

businessElements.name: MedicationAdministeredDosageRoute
businessElements.description: The SNOMED CT code (need identifier) specifying the route or physiological path of medication that was administered into or onto the patient. E.g. topical

businessElements.name: MedicationAdministeredDosageSite
businessElements.description: The SNOMED CT code (need identifier) of the anatomic site where the medication first entered the body. E.g. left arm.

businessElements.name: MedicationAdministeredDosageUnitCode
businessElements.description: This is the physical form of the product as presented to the individual.

businessElements.name: MedicationAdministeredID
businessElements.description: a unique identifier assigned by an administrative body to describe a particular medication given to a patient. The datatype InstanceIdentifier also contains data elements to identifies who / what assigned the unique id.

businessElements.name: MedicationAdministeredMedicationCode
businessElements.description: The RXNorm code for the medication the Client took. The datatype CodedElement also contains data elements to identity the codelist in RXNorm and that RXNorm is the assigning authority for the code.

businessElements.name: MedicationAdministeredNotes
businessElements.description: Notes (structured text) by the administrator of the medication

businessElements.name: MedicationAdministeredStatusCode
businessElements.description: Status of the adminstration of the medication. Except for long running administrations

businessElements.name: MedicationDispenseID
businessElements.description: Identifier assigned by the assigned authority / dispensing facility; the presciption number.

businessElements.name: MedicationDispenseOrderRefillsRemaining
businessElements.description: The number of refills remaining in an order.

businessElements.name: MedicationPrescriptionContainer
businessElements.description: A container used to associate all data elements of a prescription written medication order by a physician or other designated health professional for a medication to be dispensed by a pharmacy for administration to a patient. The prescribing practitioner may give a medication order verbally to a licensed person such as a pharmacist or a nurse. The medication may be self-administered (by patient or patient's caregiver).

businessElements.name: MedicationPrescriptionDosageQuantity
businessElements.description: The amount of medication prescribed to be given at one administration event

businessElements.name: MedicationPrescriptionDosageRoute
businessElements.description: The code (SNOMED CT) specifying the route or physiological path of administration of the medication prescribed.

businessElements.name: MedicationPrescriptionDosageSite
businessElements.description: A code ( SNOMED CT) specifying the anatomic site where the medicationhas been prescribed to first enter the body.

businessElements.name: MedicationPrescriptionID
businessElements.description: a unique identifier assigned by an administrative body of the prescriber to identify particular medication prescribed to a patient. The datatype InstanceIdentifier also contains data elements to identifies who / what assigned the unique id.

businessElements.name: MedicationPrescriptionPatientInstructions
businessElements.description: Instructions written by the prescriber as to how the medication is to be taken.

businessElements.name: MedicationPrescriptionStatusCode
businessElements.description: A code specifying the present state of the entire prescription (active

businessElements.name: PayerCoverageCollection
businessElements.description: Semantic Container for all the Semantic Elements contained in a particular instance of Insurance or Payment Coverage. There can be multiple coverages for a patient.

businessElements.name: ProblemAgeAtObservation
businessElements.description: The Client's age for the specific observation about the concern or problem

businessElements.name: ProblemConcernId
businessElements.description: a unique identifier assigned by an administrative body to a problem or concern

businessElements.name: ProblemConcernNotes
businessElements.description: General notes/comments for description of the Condition

businessElements.name: ProblemConcernStatus
businessElements.description: The code to identify the present status of the Concern or Problem.

businessElements.name: ProblemObservationCode
businessElements.description: The code used to Identify of the condition

businessElements.name: ProblemObservationId
businessElements.description: unique identifier assigned by an administrative body to specific observation of a problem or concern

businessElements.name: VitalSignBatteryEffectiveTime
businessElements.description: When the result of the tests were measured

businessElements.name: VitalSignResultEffectiveTime
businessElements.description: When the result/specime was obtained from the patient

businessElements.name: AllergyConcernID
businessElements.description: A unique identifier assigned by an administrative body to a specific allergy concern.

businessElements.name: AllergyConcernStatusCode
businessElements.description: A code representing the present status of the Allergy Concern

businessElements.name: AllergyObservationAllergenCode
businessElements.description: The substance that caused the Allergy reaction

businessElements.name: AllergiesSectionText
businessElements.description: The text for the Allergy Section

businessElements.name: AllergiesSectionTitle
businessElements.description: The Title for the Allergy Section

businessElements.name: AllergyConcernEndDate
businessElements.description: The date when the Allergy concern is no longer a concern

businessElements.name: AllergyReactionDuration
businessElements.description: The amount of time that the Adverse Reaction persisted.

businessElements.name: AllergyConcernLastKnownOccuranceDate
businessElements.description: The last known date and time of the Intolerance Condition
